reviews.review_text: I can t stop thinking about chicken fajitas after trying them here at La Casita, the sides are all great, and the chicken is perfectly seasoned, juicy, and freshly cooked. It is expensive but it lasts 2 meals. Also the service is basically absent to barely existent but I personally like that because I m just there to eat! (Thus the 5 star rating, solely based on food). You have to try La Casita!

We tried this spot tonight for the first time. It was Taco Tuesday so the tacos were on for $4 each. We tried a selection of them and they were delicious. Very fresh! We also tried the nachos and jalapeno poppers. The nachos had toppings on every bite (nacho fans will know how important this is haha) and the poppers were perfect. The service was wonderful. Friendly and charismatic staff! We also had some margaritas (mango and strawberry.) 10/10 would recommend this spot. Date spot or a night out with friends, the atmosphere suits any occasion.

We always have a great time when we go there. The food is so delicious and very authentic. The portions are very good size. The staff is very warm and friendly. Nice rustic Mexican atmosphere, downstairs, good place for parties. Our favourites are the fajitas the nachos we get both chicken and beef and their sauces are absolutely amazing! Plan to make a reservation after 730 as it gets fairly busy on weekends!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: The Food here is really good! I ordered the guacamole with two salsas (cilantro jalapeno crema and fire roasted peppers) as well as the medium Al pastor tacos. The drink is a mango mezcalita, which was good but could use a little more salt and tajin mixed in. Just tasted a little bland is all.

Great Mexican spot in Gastown. I lived abroad in central Mexico for years and can say this is the best Mexican food Ive had outside of Mexico. Everything delivered, including the staff, the music, and the food of course. I had chicken mole enchiladas and they really brought me back. The margs were great as well. Pics are only of the restaurants downstairs, the upstairs is a different vibe and also quite nice Vegetarian options: A couple decent vegetarian options Wheelchair accessibility: Accessible

We stopped in on Cinco de Mayo for a Margarita. The margaritas were very good and the chips and salsa were delicious. The staff was so friendly and welcoming. The restaurant feels like your neighborhood restaurant and you feel at home no matter where you sit. I would come back any time in Vancouver for a margarita, chips, and salsa.

The most amazing Chilaquiles that you can find Downtown!! The portion is more than excellent, and the service is warm and fast. If you wanna try chilaquiles for the first time, you can order the Chipotle ones! And dont forget to order a cafe de Olla as well!

I got the enchilada plate and Jamaica drink and loved both. I think pricing is at par with other restaurants but the food is more authentic and my plate was a big portion. The staff is great, the food is great, and I would definitely come back.

Boris, JC,l and Rosie are amazing with their service. My boyfriend and I came to this place out of random and it ended up being one of the best authentic Mexican restaurants we have been to. Food is unreal , definitely worth checking out :)
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: We came at the time the restaurant was already closing, yet the staff still allowed us in and was very welcoming. The food arrived super fast and tasted delicious. This is 100% the best and the most authentic Mexican food I had in Vancouver and probably all of BC. Friendly staff and lovely atmosphere. 10/10 Would recommend!

Great Mexican restaurant with the best chicken nachos I ve ever had. Service left a bit to be desired but they were trying hard and very pleasant. I m looking forward to going back Recommended dishes Chips & Salsa
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for choosing us! Come back soon

reviews.review_text: The food is excellent, the treatment of the employees is very friendly and the most beautiful thing of all is when I entered the restaurant they had a Pedro Infante movie on and it made me feel like I was in Mexico again   ,

Ordered combo #6 which featured a chorizo chimichanga, beef quesadilla, beans, rice, and salad. The chimichanga was outstanding. Perfectly cooked and delicious. The (half) quesadilla was also spectacular. The meal itself was not spicy to exactly my liking (I usually put ghost pepper flakes on my Mexican food - yes I like it super spicy) There were a couple bottles of hot sauce on the table, however none of them were that hot at all. But, the unnamed house hot sauce was very delicious and well rounded, just not that hot. The meal also came with a set of fried chips and some dips. One was a nice light spice dip, the other was an interesting egg and avocado or cilantro dip. Also, the table water came in a really cool (what looked like) tequila bottle. We also ordered the fish tacos and loved it! Would highly recommend going here.

I ordered a vegeterian meal, and they accidentaly gave me the meat one. When I mentioned it they were very friendly and apologized and gave me free chips + guac. Awesome place, very authentic. Drinks are 10/10 would highly recommend
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: Really beautiful ambience. We came around 6pm and it wasnt crowded. My friend and I sat in a cute place on the left side from the entrance. There were pretty paintings hung around our table. The food was really good! We ordered: wings in hot sauce (on Wednesday its $6), Casita Salad, Veggie Enchilada and Churro. The wings werent spicy for me rather had a tangy taste and paired with the blue cheese dip, it was full-on tangy salsa in my mouth. I couldnt stop eating them! My friend did find it a bit spicy but she loved it. I had the Casita Salad which was refreshing. My friend was full with delicious looking Enchilada. I had to end it with Churros! It was crunchy, sweet and sooo good! Overall really lovely place with helpful staff! Will come again!
Always get the best service here, the best tender steak tacos you will get in Vancouver!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for choosing us! Come back soon

reviews.review_text: It was the first that I went a proper Mexican restaurant and i was nkt disappointed at all. Have never a fan of tacos but they were super delicious along with some mezcal! Great vibe, great ambience, definitely going back!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! See you soon

reviews.review_text: Best classic Mexican food in town! Suiza sauce? 5 stars. Their gorgeous creamy salsa verde? 116 stars. Always a good time.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: Randomly came here while walking around. Was fairly busy upstairs. The service was great and fast with friendly staff. It was taco Tuesday so i tried 4 different kinds... Delicious! Washed it down with a lime margarita.. would definatly recommend stopping here..
As a Mexican I felt at home, easy one of the best Mexican places put there, I might be able to get over the boarder but I can t get over their food.

This place is a real gem. I ve been coming here for years. The owners run a tight ship. The food tastes fresher than most Vancouver restaurant fair - my favourite of the many other Mexican restaurants in the area.
Never disappoints. My go to when in the area. Great service and even better food.
Such delicious food. Had a lovely family birthday dinner and the staff were so welcoming and generous. Dietary restrictions: Lots of gluten free options
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: Food was delicious! Best mexican food in town. The ones with the most authentic mexican flavor yet. It is a little expensive, but its totally worth it. The service was incredible too! Super nice staff, helpful and friendly.
Very good food. Service was also great. We had the enchiladas and fajitas and some delicious margaritas
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you! hope you come back soon. :D <3

reviews.review_text: Love this place! Very friendly staff with great service! JC our server was excellent! And the food? Delicious!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: Just had dinner here amd it was so delicious! Staff are super friendly and fast service with a very welcoming atmosphere. Will definately be back.
Im not a professor in Mexican cuisine, but for me it seemed like a great place to eat proper Mexican! Love the Chimichanga for sure! Fair prices, good food, even better drinks

My first time trying Mex food in town couldnt be better! I went to La Casita with mexican friends and we loved it! By the way, they said this place represents Mexico really well and its authentic cousine. I got the Combination #1
Fantastic tacos for taco Tuesday. The beef were my favourite but would also recommend the carnitas and the chorizo. Service was great, would definitely return!
The food was really mouth watering :) Loved the vibe in there as well. Tortilla soup is a must try
I love this place , is very Mexican! The food is well cook, good flavor and ingredients fresh
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! See you soon

reviews.review_text: Good food, big portions, fast service
really good tacos, large portions and very good service
Lunch... comida corrida. Drink,  soup  main, dessert. Was very good.  Its a very good mexican food to try, specially for the price, and for the portion was big. You gonna get full.
Hadnt been to this busy small Mexican restaurant for awhile. Didnt disappoint as the burritos were excellent with authentic flavors and spice kevel.
Super good everyone so nice and happy to serve you,  all dishes so delicious,  definitely I will go back
Had a great date night with my boyfriend at La Casita in gastown. Great drinks and delicious Mexican food. We will be back!
The food was sooo good, real authentic Mexican restaurant and it was so good I forgot to take pictures but the churros wow amazing!!
Best Mexican place in the lower mainland for sure. The chicken tacos were soooooo gooooood!!

sooooo much fun!!! an amazing atmosphere and impeccable service, from the host at the door to the service and management. we went on cinco de mayo and had the strawberry super margs, which were delicious, fresh strawberry puree and everything. Would be my top restaurant recommendation if you are going to gastown! They also hooked us up with some fun merch which we did not expect but was a fun surprise!! We had the best time!! 100/10!!!
Great food and awesome staff.  Margaritas were tasty as well.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Come back soon! It was our pleasure

reviews.review_text: Absolutely love this place. I have been here many times . The staff are awesome and the food is delicious. The portions are very large and we always have some left to take home . I highly recommend La Casita !

I visit lacasita probably 2-3 times a year, and its always such a treat! I drive an hour just to eat here. Its so authentic and delicious. Never a disappointment. Last time I ordered a salad served in a tortilla shell. It was so heavenly. And you cant forget the amazing chips and salsa that come with every table once you order! And if you really want a treat, order the flan! A melt in your mouth desert!

Delicious food! Had the tacos al pastor. Please note the reason it s $16 is because your about to get served a massive plate of joy, not 3 teeny tacos. You get a freaking platter of beans, rice, salad, pico, a thing of salsa verde, and really big hearty tacos on amazing tortillas. And they bring you chips and salsa while you wait for foodZ

OUR FAVORITE!! We searched all evening (last minute after 9PM) for Latin American food for my niece on her 14th birthday. They came from Miami to Vancouver to stay since Christmas and every outing has been awful! We walked out of a few locations on a night out, due to unfriendly customer service. we FINALLY had a successful and accidental find of this place tonight at 9:30PM on a Tuesday night! WOW Im absolutely recommending this place to all! Our server Omar was extremely helpful and nice. He made her a special virgin Pina Colada in a giant Fish Bowl and  even brought out candle lit churro and helped us sing Happy Birthday! This place went above and beyond anything weve seen since being here.. We found our new favorite place and with a wonderful menu and beautiful atmosphere right in the heart of gas town, it cant be beat!
This place is a must visit, the staff are so friendly, the food was brought relatively quick, and the taste is amazing, 5 stars all the way!!!

Courteous and efficient service. The food tastes fresh, and it was brought promptly to the table. Great selection of drinks. The mix of music played at a good volume. The place was kept clean and well ventilated so you dont walk away smelling the food you ate.
Great food!  Amazingly festive mole sauce with a hidden heat. Portions are large. Great service and atmosphere. Thanks for the great experience.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Jason! We love to hear you enjoyed our Mole!! :)

reviews.review_text: Amazing tacos, margaritas get them double and mango! They don t play with the salsa here not just sliced and diced tomatoes onions. Will keep coming back
Best DELIVERED Mexican of all time in all places (in Vancouver), period. and Doordash gets a one star rating so technically this is a six star review Food

Went to La Casita for the first time. The food was amazing. Everything was perfect from the main entree to the sides including the guacamole. Everyone in my family loved it . Portions were perfect size. We had a little of everything and even my picky kid finished her plate.

I loved this place!!! Everyone is so kind and ready for every request. I went with a Mexican friend and she approved every dish. I thought that the food wasnt that cheap but when I saw the size of a plate I changed my idea, I think the prices are balanced.
My first try for Mexican cuisine. Everything are delicious though I dont actually know what Im eating And the waitress was really nice even though that day are raving busy.
Had a great lunch here.  Tasty and well priced.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! See you soon

reviews.review_text: One of the best Mexican Restaurant that I have visited here in Vancouver, Good taste, nice service, and really chill experience. Maybe is just a little bit expensive over my expectations, but I understand that s the price here for Mexican food So highly recommend!

First time visit, totally recommend! 5/5! Friendly staff, sweet margaritas.. and the food? Just amazing! Had chicken burrito and some texas nachos to share.. absolutely delicious! Went there on Wednesday evening, pretty full house. Good to book a table if youre 4+ of your dinning party. Theres also downstairs that fits like 50 people, awesome for christmas/company party!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: Love it!! We had the wings as an appetizer and they were just how we like them. My husband had the potato flautas, and honestly I didnt think he would like them but he loved them. I think I liked them more than my meal. Very reasonably priced also. I would definitely go back

Great food. Friendly staff and relatively quick service. They have a really clean restaurant with the dopest sinks Ive ever seen. You get a lot of food for the price. Not game changing but all the food here is done really well. Would recommend for large groups. Staff is really accommodating. They have endless chips and dips.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: It was amazing food and cheap price. Friendly server and good atmosphere. Definitely want to come back again and drink beer with food.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: The food is really good, everything taste amazing. Just a bit slow in delivering food for large groups.
Fantastic Mexican food! Just delicious. Authentic, tasty, wonderful. Highly recommend.
the best food and the best service!! I love the drinks and i love the ppl there! Highly recommend the beef fajitas!

This was my first visit to this restaurant on the recommendation of my dear friend, Lori Hussey. I had Huevos Rancheros for the first time, and it was fantastic. My friend ordered the Tortilla Soup, which looked amazing. I was so sorry that I only had one stomach, because I wanted to try it. It looked and smelled so good. Please consider this for your next Mexican meal in downtown Vancouver if you live here.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much!!!

reviews.review_text: We went here because we were waiting on another place and boy were we lucky. The food here is out of this world. This was a family meal and the staff were so friendly and welcoming even though we had no reservation at 6pm on a Friday. The dinner was wonderful and we were served extremely quickly without feeling rushed. One of the nicest dining experiences I have had in Vancouver.

Great place to have authentic Mexican food. The portions are very generous and the food is delicious. The service provided by the bar tenders is fantastic. This is my favorite go to Mexican restaurant. Gracias!
Vegetarians, trust me- order the #7 combo and you won t be disappointed. The BEST vegetarian Mexican I ve had in a long time!
Authentic, delicious, amazing atmosphere, super attentive staff. A personal favorite!

My wife and I had a pretty damn great time. We tried many different items on the menu and overall the meal was great.  There were items I didn t enjoy, but I fell that s personal taste and not the quality of the food. Everything seemed cooked well and the server Adrian was very kind and helpful. Going to have to come back and try this again as there s more items on the menu to explore. Thanks again, Adrian!
LOVED the flavor and freshness. Very good service. Margaritas great too!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: Lovely servers. Great prices and fun ambiance Look out for their daily deals Food
Amazing, authentic Mexican cuisine. The staff were very friendly and accommodating to my food allergy. Very affordable as well. Recommendation for vegetarians Highly recommend
This is definitely a great place for some delicious Mexican eats !
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: One of our favourite Mexican restaurants in all of Vancouver. Vibes, service and food are all great! I had a birthday here recently and reserved a big table downstairs. It was a cozy private space that made my birthday memorable. The fishbowl margaritas helped too!

I had a few minutes before my appointment and then I saw Our Lady of Guadalupe in the window I knew this would be a good place for a quick cuppa tea or a bowl of hot soup. She was right, the people were welcoming and the soup was excellent. God Bless
Amazing food, friendly waiters, nice decor. Food was authentic Mexican.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: Was there on the 15th, and really felt at home (Mexico) great ambience good food and excellent service. Its one if not the most accurate mexican restaurant Ive found in town. Totally recommend it if you want to have some authentic mexican food.
Really good food amazing staff good prices. Will definitely be going back

SOOOOOO Good! When we went to Vancouver for a concert, I asked where was the best place to eat good Mexican and we were NOT disappointed! Fantastic margaritas, amazon poppers, everything was fresh and delicious and the entire team was super attentive! Will be back for sure!
Really good food and service. We sat outside which was nice
Tried burritos with shangria,it was amazing  . Portion was big enough , really nice place to try for Mexican food.
The food was mouthwatering and filling. The atmosphere was great as was the service!
Cinco de mayo was a blast here! Awesome service and a wonderful owner who hooked us up with some great swag including a Hammock!
Just had a delicious meal with a super yummy Margarita!!! Lovely ambience in a fantastic location. Big portions, so lots of leftovers too
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: Fantastic tacos on Tuesday. Carnitas was the best but the rest are very good too!
The servers were excellent. The food was fantastic. Will definitely be back. Their brunch sounds like a good reason to go back.
Good & Fresh Food. Actually taste like Mexican Food. Clean washroom.

The second time I visited La Casita and it was even better than my last visit! I had beef chimichangas and the tortilla was crispy and delightful and was brought out to me piping hot! Service was very quick considering how strapped for employees places like this are nowdays. Top notch food top notch service 10/10! Love you guys

I was there with a group of friends and we had a great time  food was delicious, margaritas were really good, service and attention was amazing even been we were 18 people. Good place to try Mexican food in Vancouver.

One of my fav places in Vancouver!!! My boyfriend and I have been consistently coming back to this restaurant almost every day for 2 weeks so far!!! I m actually not very familiar with Mexican cuisine and I am a very picky eater, but their food feels very soulful! Simple clean and good quality ingredients. Makes me want to cry   !! EVERYTHING we ve ordered so far has all been consistently great!! After one bite, you want one more bite never get tired of any of their dishes! I love La Casita!!! It deserves to be heard and tried out by more people!

We tried La Casita last night on the recommendation of friends. It was an absolute delight! Service was great, staff super friendly and prompt. We both enjoyed the enchiladas. Huge portions, hot and delicious! The homemade sauces that came with the appetizer chips were so fresh and tasty. Overall great experience, nice room and very good price point. We will be back!

Visited here looking for a hearty brunch and was not disappointed. The food was delicious and our server was very friendly. I had the eggs Benedict which was delicious and particularly enjoyed the potatoes. Also, when our server asked if we wanted chips, I was surprised to find that they came with 3 different kinds of sauce, each one delicious in their own right. My favourite was the green one... that wasnt guacomole... dont know the name. Youll just have to go and find out!
Simply incredible. Omg I want to eat there again.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much! See you soon

reviews.review_text: Have you been to playa del carmen? Cancun? how about tijuana? ........ No! .. well come to La casita here in gastown Vancouver. Its basically a little slice of our beautiful next Next door neighbour Mexico. Try the tacos... some ceviche and a mexican BULLDOG... Yup theyve got em. My server Pablo was continuously on the move but also made plenty of time for get my order correct and precise. Hes great ... ask for him when you here he really does enjoy what he does. Hes got some great recommendations.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the great review!

reviews.review_text: Good food and great place to sit outside in the nice weather.
Great food. Pretty fair prices if you go during prom days, like Monday for burritos and margaritas is perfect and taco Tuesday is awesome. I would absolutely recommend it to everyone.
Fantastic. Great drink. Great food. Authentic. The soups are amazing.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your great review!

reviews.review_text: Authentic Mexican brunch which was super delicious!  Good portions and food came quickly.  Even the coffee was good.  Friendly and efficient service. Will definitely return.
Super friendly staff, and I love the low lighting.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Loved to hear that! Visit us again!

reviews.review_text: This is a great spot if youre hosting a birthday party. Great atmosphere, great drinks, and even better food. Thanks again team!
